pecially the girl child. “In his remarks, the Deputy Governor, Kastina State, Alhaji Mannir Yakubu identifies illiteracy and unemployment as a major threat to society. “Alhaji Yakubu said Kastina State  Government is prepared to work with UBEC to increase the number of such centres so that the girl child in Kastina will have access to proper education. “The deputy governor commended UBEC and Senator Saddique Yar Adua for his role initiating the project in the state.” Vanguard News Nigeria The United Nations Children Fund (UNICEF), says Nigeria is losing out on a literate and skilled workforce it needs to grow economically due to huge number of out of school children. October 10, 2018 In "Education" As Nigeria's  education sector continues to experience a decline  in standard and quality of infrastructure, the Executive Secretary, Universal Basic Education Commission, UBEC, Dr Hamid Bobboyi has said  the most worrisome issue was the out-of-school children phenomenon. He said: “The most worrisome issue is the out-of-school children phenomenon as the… July 12, 2018 In "Education" By Joseph Erunke - Abuja Executive Secretary of Universal Basic Education Commission, UBEC, Dr Hamid Bobboyi, has appealed to stakeholders to join hands with the federal government in ensuring that the quality of teaching and learning at the basic level of education in Nigeria is strengthened for the graduates of… January 10, 2021 In "Education"